01:55.659 --> 01:58.256
- Prudhomme.
- John, sorry to call you so early.

01:58.556 --> 01:59.955
- I was up.
- We got a problem.

02:06.446 --> 02:08.145
What time is it?

02:11.043 --> 02:12.840
It's early.

02:13.940 --> 02:15.837
OK. I'll make you some breakfast.

02:18.036 --> 02:20.730
I don't have time.
Go back to sleep.

02:33.422 --> 02:36.318
Yeah. The old man says,
"Son, I get a hard-on once a week...

02:36.518 --> 02:39.414
but I fart at least
ten times a day".

02:40.912 --> 02:43.410
- Good morning, John.
- Keep them away, Mac.

02:43.610 --> 02:43.875
OK. Stay back!

02:43.910 --> 02:45.908
- You've been inside?
- No, I just got here.

02:48.007 --> 02:50.502
Hey, how does a blonde turn
the lights on after sex?

02:51.201 --> 02:52.799
She opens the car door.

02:54.698 --> 02:57.695
- I don't know why I waste my good jokes on you.
- I don't know either.

03:01.191 --> 03:03.788
Prudhomme. What are
you doing here?

03:04.188 --> 03:07.084
- I got the call.
- Bullshit. We were at the scene first.

03:07.284 --> 03:09.781
- I got the call!
- What's the deal, man?

03:09.981 --> 03:11.779
You don't have enough cases
that you need more?

03:12.079 --> 03:14.178
- Where's the body?
- I asked you a question.

03:14.376 --> 03:16.374
Hey! He just doing what
they told him to do.

03:16.974 --> 03:18.237
Hollinsworth, I'm not talking to you.

03:18.272 --> 03:20.969
Oh, you're not talking to me, Scholfield?
Yeah, well... I'm talking to you.

03:21.468 --> 03:23.666
So what is it?
You better than everybody else?

03:23.965 --> 03:26.164
Nobody can do as good as you?
We're all idiots here?

03:26.464 --> 03:28.163
I don't see the point
of this conversation.

03:28.463 --> 03:31.461
The point is the reason why
nobody likes you.

03:33.958 --> 03:35.156
I like you.

03:45.646 --> 03:49.543
He's a little ripe, but a...
He's been dead for four days.

03:52.038 --> 03:55.233
- Who is he?
- Peter Balcour. He owned the place.

03:56.433 --> 03:57.433
Who found him?

03:57.633 --> 04:00.080
Contractor who had
an appointment with him.

04:00.115 --> 04:02.528
Seems Balcour's old man was
bit of a recluse.

04:02.727 --> 04:04.591
Owned a large fleet of fishing boats.

04:04.626 --> 04:05.923
He died a couple of months ago
and left everything to his son...

04:06.421 --> 04:08.321
Balcour had an appointment
with the contractor...

04:08.421 --> 04:09.718
...to fix the place up to sell it.

04:12.915 --> 04:14.515
Any other family?

04:14.715 --> 04:17.012
Contractor says the kid
was the end of the line.

04:17.209 --> 04:19.509
- Anything taken?
- You mean besides his arm?

04:21.805 --> 04:26.702
No. We did find his wallet in his
jacket pocket with 112 dollars in.

04:29.199 --> 04:30.897
Was he alive when
he lost the arm?

04:31.097 --> 04:34.495
Yeah. If you check out
the blood splatter.

04:34.795 --> 04:36.293
But... take a look at this.

04:37.890 --> 04:40.788
He got some kind of
strange burn effect here.

04:40.988 --> 04:43.483
And the back of his
head is all singed.

04:43.783 --> 04:46.082
- What is it?
- I don't know.

04:46.481 --> 04:49.379
I'll have to verify all that
when I get him back to the shop.

04:49.778 --> 04:50.878
Any more light in here?

04:50.978 --> 04:53.473
No, that's it. I didn't wanna touch
anything so I left the curtains closed.

04:53.972 --> 04:55.271
- Open them.
- Sure.

05:20.845 --> 05:23.342
- You finished that report?
- Yeah.

05:23.442 --> 05:23.541
- Thanks.
- OK.

05:24.940 --> 05:27.137
Do you think this guy is
somewhere in New York city?

05:27.237 --> 05:30.335
I'll get in touch with NYPD
and when they get him, I'll get his ass!

05:34.932 --> 05:37.829
Hey Jack, can I get one
of those papers?

05:38.926 --> 05:42.124
Prudhomme, Hollinsworth.
In my office.

05:45.619 --> 05:49.017
Rousch and Scholfield were just in here
bitching about you stealing their case.

05:49.217 --> 05:50.616
They can have it if they want it.

05:50.816 --> 05:54.211
This is not a democracy, Prudhomme.
It's your case.

05:54.510 --> 05:56.707
- I gave it to you.
- Then what's the problem?

05:57.007 --> 05:59.404
The problem is you pissed 'em off.

06:02.401 --> 06:05.699
Hollinsworth is the only one in the entire
department who wants to work with you.

06:05.998 --> 06:07.996
I don't know what it was
like in New Orleans...

06:08.296 --> 06:11.192
but since you came here you've gone
through one partner after another.

06:11.493 --> 06:14.689
Did you bring me in here to talk
about my social skills?

06:15.189 --> 06:17.287
Talking to you is like
pissing into the wind.

06:17.487 --> 06:19.485
I bet you should know
better by now.

06:21.182 --> 06:22.281
What've you got?

06:23.481 --> 06:27.674
Peter Balcour, 33 year old, male.

06:28.174 --> 06:30.273
Owned a fleet of fishing boats.

06:30.573 --> 06:32.771
Had his right arm cut
off at the shoulder.

06:33.070 --> 06:35.369
The killer presumably
took it with him when he left.

06:35.569 --> 06:38.167
Took it with him?
You mean like a souvenir?

06:40.362 --> 06:42.261
That's somethin' new.
Witnesses?

06:42.561 --> 06:45.458
No, but the killer
left us a message...

06:45.658 --> 06:47.455
...written in blood.

06:47.755 --> 06:49.653
- Prints?
- Forensics is checking.

06:49.853 --> 06:53.449
- We won't find any prints.
- How the hell do you know that?

06:53.749 --> 06:55.946
Because he doesn't want us to.

06:56.546 --> 07:00.242
- And also, there will be more bodies.
- You don't know that.

07:00.541 --> 07:03.639
- For all you know, this... What's his name?
- Balcour.

07:03.739 --> 07:06.137
Balcour shorted a customer
on a case of tuna.

07:06.337 --> 07:10.132
The guy cut his arm off and pulled
all this bullshit to throw us off track.

07:10.431 --> 07:13.826
The killer wrote "He is
coming" on the window.

07:14.326 --> 07:18.023
That signifies a future event
that hasn't taken place yet.

07:18.423 --> 07:22.617
This guy has something worked out
and today was just the first move.

07:23.516 --> 07:26.512
If this was all planned,
what's the motive?

07:29.411 --> 07:33.407
We already know the motive.
The killer wanted his arm.

07:33.807 --> 07:35.706
That's a motive.

07:52.888 --> 07:56.783
Would it be too much to ask to get
a cheeseburger every once in a while?

07:58.681 --> 08:01.478
What do you think
he took the arm for?

08:02.077 --> 08:04.475
We have to talk
about this over lunch?

08:04.775 --> 08:09.271
I don't know. Obviously we're not dealing with
somebody who is playing with a full deck here.

08:09.571 --> 08:11.568
God only knows what he is doing.

08:11.867 --> 08:14.264
Maybe we got another
Jeffrey Dahmer.

08:14.962 --> 08:17.160
Why not take the whole body?

08:17.460 --> 08:19.759
Maybe he only wanted a snack.

08:35.942 --> 08:39.840
Jenny called today.
She's coming to visit us.

08:40.140 --> 08:41.438
Again?

08:41.639 --> 08:44.934
Yes, again.
What, is there a problem?

08:45.134 --> 08:47.830
No but the last time she
came for a weekend...

08:48.130 --> 08:50.527
...she stayed two weeks.

08:50.727 --> 08:53.824
She's my best friend. What I'm supposed
to tell her? Stay in a hotel?

08:58.619 --> 09:00.316
Hey, you OK?

09:01.515 --> 09:03.513
Yeah. Just... thinking.

09:03.913 --> 09:08.109
About that case?
I saw it on the news.

09:09.808 --> 09:12.404
This world just keep getting sicker
and sicker everyday.

09:13.601 --> 09:15.000
Why would someone do
such a thing?

09:15.201 --> 09:16.798
I don't want to talk about it.

09:16.998 --> 09:19.596
Well, I'm not asking details.
I'm just asking your opinion.

09:19.895 --> 09:22.992
I said I don't want
to talk about it!

10:04.149 --> 10:08.746
And the fat guy says: I thought I was gonna
scream when he came out of the closet.

10:09.546 --> 10:10.545
Prudhomme.

10:12.043 --> 10:13.541
Do you know the exact cause of death?

10:13.741 --> 10:18.334
Yeah. Exsanguination. That means
he bled to death.

10:19.034 --> 10:24.529
He also has some burns on the right
side of his parietal region.

10:24.829 --> 10:28.524
Looks like he was tortured with a
taser or some kind of cattle prod.

10:28.824 --> 10:30.224
It didn't kill him but
probably knocked him out.

10:30.622 --> 10:33.718
So he was unconscious when
the arm was taken?

10:33.918 --> 10:35.817
No, unfortunately, he was.

10:36.016 --> 10:39.314
His endorphin and adrenaline levels
were incredible high in his blood.

10:39.513 --> 10:41.613
Which means he was
wide awake. He...

10:42.113 --> 10:44.310
He experienced a severe
trauma just before he died.

10:44.410 --> 10:48.005
You tell me that he waited for him
to wake up before he cut his arm off?

10:48.305 --> 10:51.101
- Yeah, that's what I'm telling you.
- How sick is that?

10:51.201 --> 10:52.099
I can also tell you that
whoever this guy is...

10:52.299 --> 10:53.299
...he knows what he is doing...

10:53.399 --> 10:56.497
...because he removed that arm
with almost surgical precision.

10:56.697 --> 11:00.393
This guy is no Jack the Ripper.
You might be interested in this.

11:02.589 --> 11:04.986
- Roman numerals.
- What's that?

11:05.185 --> 11:09.882
Oh, yeah. It's a keymark
etched in permanently.

11:18.173 --> 11:20.270
Let me check the neck.

11:34.554 --> 11:36.954
Bismark Locker Services.

11:41.649 --> 11:43.049
Over there.

11:46.944 --> 11:48.042
Bingo!

12:07.021 --> 12:08.220
Can you identify it?

12:09.919 --> 12:12.617
Brachychiton acerifolius.

12:13.016 --> 12:14.914
It's a flower from the bottle tree.

12:15.515 --> 12:16.978
Where can I find it around here?

12:17.013 --> 12:20.907
- You can't. It's indigenous to Australia.
- We're not in Australia.

12:21.207 --> 12:23.405
I can see why they
made you detective.

12:23.605 --> 12:27.501
- What about the Botanical Museum?
- I don't think so.

12:27.801 --> 12:31.097
This flower was picked
only a few days ago.

12:31.597 --> 12:35.292
There is one, however,
at the Botanical Gardens.

12:45.484 --> 12:47.083
There's your flower.

12:47.382 --> 12:49.378
- Billy?
- Got it.

13:02.265 --> 13:03.865
Hey, Prudhomme.

13:04.662 --> 13:07.159
This whole area has been
cut out and laid back in.

13:18.848 --> 13:21.344
- Pull it up.
- Why not?

13:31.533 --> 13:32.532
Oh, my God...

13:35.030 --> 13:36.228
Jesus!

13:50.614 --> 13:54.711
Call Chibley and
close this place down.

14:01.304 --> 14:04.102
How difficult could it be for someone
to get in here at night?

14:04.401 --> 14:08.895
Not very difficult. All we have is
a wall around the property.

14:09.294 --> 14:10.594
No security?

14:10.993 --> 14:14.290
This isn't a bank.
All we have are plants here.

14:14.490 --> 14:15.589
Prudhomme?

14:25.876 --> 14:26.876
Andy...

14:30.672 --> 14:32.770
His arm has been removed.

14:35.768 --> 14:37.163
What's that?

14:42.861 --> 14:45.057
This guy likes to play
with numbers, doesn't he?

14:52.250 --> 14:55.748
Prints identify him as
Matthew Leesan, age 33.

14:56.147 --> 14:57.844
He works for the I.R.S.

14:58.044 --> 15:00.543
At least our killer's taste
in victims is improving.

15:00.743 --> 15:05.338
He was killed before Balcour
and at a different location.

15:05.639 --> 15:07.634
The killer moved his
body to the Gardens.

15:07.934 --> 15:10.431
Why go to all that trouble?
Risk being seen?

15:10.531 --> 15:12.030
What about the numbers
on the victims?

15:12.230 --> 15:13.927
- Actually, they're numerals.
- What?

15:14.027 --> 15:15.926
- They're roman numerals.
- And numerals aren't numbers?

15:16.226 --> 15:21.120
All I'm saying is I think the killer
choose numerals for a reason.

15:21.920 --> 15:24.017
119...

15:24.216 --> 15:27.713
2427.

15:28.711 --> 15:30.511
Numbers, numerals.

15:30.711 --> 15:33.606
So far, we've only found
what he wanted us to find.

15:33.806 --> 15:37.104
No prints. No trace evidence. Nothing.

15:37.304 --> 15:39.798
What we have here is a
very clever serial killer.

15:43.296 --> 15:45.495
Guys, the lab just called down.

15:45.994 --> 15:48.092
The blood on the window
wasn't Balcour's.

15:48.292 --> 15:51.390
- Whose was it? Killer's?
- It wasn't anybody's.

15:51.990 --> 15:53.585
Lab says it wasn't human.

15:53.885 --> 15:55.786
Says it was lamb's blood.

16:31.147 --> 16:32.947
Do you wanna play?

16:34.444 --> 16:36.142
That's it, my baby.

16:37.041 --> 16:39.040
You wanna play?

17:38.377 --> 17:39.676
No!

17:56.358 --> 17:57.357
- Who called it in?
- I did.

17:57.657 --> 17:59.756
- Where is it?
- Just over here.

18:02.951 --> 18:04.151
Right down here, gentleman.

18:05.549 --> 18:07.748
Watch yourselves,
it's a mess down here.

18:07.948 --> 18:11.145
Transients, druggies, whatever...

18:13.439 --> 18:16.037
All sorts of shit
happens down here.

18:16.936 --> 18:18.535
Fuck! It stinks!

18:18.735 --> 18:22.334
Yeah, it's too easy to go outside
to relieve themselves.

18:22.533 --> 18:26.727
- How did you come across him?
- One of his buddies flagged us down.

18:37.914 --> 18:40.313
Rats in this city!

18:44.207 --> 18:47.206
Here is something you
don't see every day.

18:49.303 --> 18:50.902
He's in there.

19:14.277 --> 19:15.775
Oh my God!

19:19.072 --> 19:20.271
Oh my God!

19:26.964 --> 19:28.561
Oh my God!

19:29.860 --> 19:31.458
What's this guy got?

19:31.558 --> 19:34.256
Fucking shopping list or something?

19:35.455 --> 19:37.455
Where's his head?

19:42.049 --> 19:46.444
There's a guy sitting in front of me here
without his head, John. Where's his head?

19:48.242 --> 19:49.641
I'm sorry.

19:55.337 --> 19:56.936
Where is Chibley?

19:57.135 --> 19:58.732
He's on his way.

20:02.328 --> 20:06.123
One plastic comb, about
1.25 in change and a pack of gum.

20:06.423 --> 20:09.721
Oh yeah, and a wallet.
One James Ordway.

20:10.020 --> 20:11.120
- You done?
- Yeah.

20:11.420 --> 20:13.617
I got a pretty good
idea what killed him.

20:13.817 --> 20:15.913
- Is this the scene?
- No.

20:16.212 --> 20:19.310
The killer cut him in here...

20:19.510 --> 20:23.306
strung him up and then he
bled him like a stuck pig.

20:23.705 --> 20:26.103
Then he dragged him back in there,
cleaned him up...

20:26.303 --> 20:29.997
...and sat him on the throne
for a dramatic effect.

20:30.995 --> 20:33.594
- I gotta get some air.
- You're welcome.

20:40.388 --> 20:42.185
- Any witnesses?
- No.

20:42.784 --> 20:45.282
What? No witnesses?
No witnesses?

20:45.481 --> 20:47.478
- Are you kidding me?
- We talked to everyone in the building...

20:47.578 --> 20:48.877
...no one saw anything.
No one heard anything.

20:49.076 --> 20:51.677
Wait a minute! You're kidding me.
A guy gets in here...

20:51.777 --> 20:53.275
...cuts another guy's head off...

20:53.573 --> 20:56.174
...walks off with it
and nobody sees anything?

20:56.273 --> 20:58.272
No witnesses! Fuck!

20:58.771 --> 21:02.066
I swear to God, man. I've
been on the job 8 years...

21:02.366 --> 21:06.560
...I've never seen anythin'
like this. Never!

21:08.059 --> 21:12.256
- He wants to shock us.
- He's doin' a good job.

21:13.254 --> 21:14.554
Let's go.

21:18.148 --> 21:21.445
We found the victim's wallet.
Driver's license ID'd him as James Ordway.

21:21.844 --> 21:22.609
Are we sure it's him?

21:22.644 --> 21:25.042
Yeah. We checked the prints
against the license. It's him.

21:25.142 --> 21:28.039
Leesan was killed 2 weeks ago,
Balcour one week ago...

21:28.239 --> 21:30.336
- Ordway, last night.
- We're up to speed.

21:30.536 --> 21:33.132
I had the lab blow up
his license photo.

21:49.014 --> 21:53.711
2427...

22:02.801 --> 22:04.702
119...

22:05.101 --> 22:09.895
Numbers...
1 plus 1 plus 9. 2.

22:13.192 --> 22:18.586
2 plus 4...

22:30.575 --> 22:34.569
4 plus 2 plus 7...

22:35.367 --> 22:39.563
5... Doesn't make sense.
Doesn't make sense.

22:55.347 --> 23:02.042
Peter, 119...
119...

23:05.937 --> 23:09.631
Peter 1:19...

23:11.830 --> 23:14.130
My God! Peter 1:19...

23:14.328 --> 23:16.626
Mathew 24:27...

23:28.913 --> 23:31.911
Peter, Matthew, James.
All names of apostles.

23:32.210 --> 23:35.805
Peter was a fisherman. Balcour
owned a fishing fleet.

23:36.105 --> 23:39.701
Mathew was a tax collector.
Leesan worked for the I.R.S.

23:40.300 --> 23:42.299
So the guy is some kind
of a zealot?

23:42.799 --> 23:46.793
The numbers he carved on the victims
are chapter and verses from the Bible.

23:47.193 --> 23:51.586
Peter, chapter 1, verse 19.
119.

23:51.986 --> 23:54.686
"But with precious blood
as of a lamb...

23:54.885 --> 23:58.282
...unblemished and
unspotted. Christ...

23:58.781 --> 24:01.081
...a message was written
in lamb's blood".

24:01.580 --> 24:03.978
Matthew, 24:27.

24:04.277 --> 24:08.872
"For as the lightning cometh out of the
east, and shineth unto the west,

24:09.272 --> 24:12.867
so shall also be the coming
of the Son of man".

24:13.566 --> 24:16.764
All the victims were 33 years old.
The same age as Christ...

24:16.963 --> 24:18.261
...when he died.

24:18.561 --> 24:21.157
All three died a week
apart of each other...

24:21.357 --> 24:23.455
...on a Friday, the
same day Christ died.

24:23.655 --> 24:26.352
The guy is rebuilding
the body of Christ.

24:26.852 --> 24:29.149
You say he's actually
rebuilding a body?

24:29.349 --> 24:33.247
Yes. He's killed a person a week
for the last 3 weeks.

24:33.347 --> 24:34.245
He's halfway through.

24:34.545 --> 24:37.141
If he stays on his Friday schedule,
that'll take 3 more weeks.

24:37.341 --> 24:41.137
- What's 3 weeks from now?
- Easter.

24:41.736 --> 24:43.335
The resurrection.

24:47.530 --> 24:49.530
Scholfield, you and Rousch
contact...

24:49.729 --> 24:51.924
...every seminar, school
and church in the area.

24:52.124 --> 24:54.222
Check on zealots,
disturbed personalities...

24:54.522 --> 24:56.122
Anyone who might fit the profile.

24:56.321 --> 24:59.119
Moltz, check the mental institutions...

24:59.319 --> 25:02.517
- ... see if they ever treated anyone that could be our boy.
- Got it.

25:02.816 --> 25:07.010
The rest should canvas the crime scenes again.
Somebody had to see something!

25:19.697 --> 25:20.897
Care a beer later?

25:21.197 --> 25:24.791
No I can't, I promised Sara
I'd go to the market...

25:25.091 --> 25:27.188
...so the house is stocked
when Jenny comes in.

25:28.388 --> 25:32.784
What's the story with this Jenny?
Is she cute?

25:35.780 --> 25:37.177
I guess so.

25:37.676 --> 25:40.874
You guess so? She's cute.
She's cute, right?

25:41.173 --> 25:43.371
OK, so what's the problem?
You know I'm cute.

25:43.471 --> 25:46.071
Can we make a little connection here?
You'll hook us up?

25:46.370 --> 25:51.166
I don't know... That's all I need is for her start
liking you and I've to see her longer.

25:51.465 --> 25:54.659
No, no. That's good.
She likes me, she can stay with me.

25:54.959 --> 25:57.058
It's all good. We all win.

25:58.157 --> 26:00.255
Are you really that desperate?

26:01.054 --> 26:03.653
Yeah. I really am.

26:32.721 --> 26:36.018
Father Rousell dropped by
to see how we're doing.

26:36.418 --> 26:40.212
- Good to see you, John.
- What brings you by, Father?

26:40.612 --> 26:43.608
Well, it's been 6 months
since you've been to church.

26:44.008 --> 26:45.907
I just wanted to see how you're doing.

26:48.204 --> 26:49.902
I'm fine.

26:50.901 --> 26:53.200
Will you sit down?
I'll just get some coffee.

26:53.898 --> 26:55.395
I'm just fine.

26:56.795 --> 26:59.793
You shouldn't turn your
back on your faith.

27:00.293 --> 27:01.691
God loves you, John.

27:01.991 --> 27:03.890
His love can help you heal.

27:04.189 --> 27:06.188
Oh, I've seen how he loves me.

27:06.788 --> 27:10.082
My son was in a coma
for 5 days.

27:10.382 --> 27:12.880
You know how many times I prayed?

27:13.280 --> 27:16.075
Where was my God when
I needed him?

27:23.669 --> 27:28.762
- I'm sorry.
- It's alright. It's alright.

27:35.956 --> 27:38.952
What the hell were
you thinking, Sara?

27:40.449 --> 27:42.348
I can't reach you anymore.

27:42.647 --> 27:44.845
I'm right here.

27:50.938 --> 27:53.837
I'm worried about you.

27:54.336 --> 27:56.731
I'm worried about us.

27:57.231 --> 27:58.630
What do you want from me?

27:59.229 --> 28:01.428
I want you to talk to me.

28:01.928 --> 28:03.925
Will you please just
talk to me?

28:09.523 --> 28:13.518
It's been 1 year
since Michael died...

28:13.917 --> 28:16.414
...and you have not visited
his grave since the funeral.

28:18.211 --> 28:19.811
You don't understand.

28:20.110 --> 28:24.807
You are not the only
one who lost a child!

28:30.198 --> 28:31.897
I'm sorry.

28:32.596 --> 28:33.495
I'm sorry.

28:35.894 --> 28:37.492
I'm so sorry.

28:37.592 --> 28:39.590
I didn't mean that.

28:52.374 --> 28:54.373
- Morning, John.
- Hi.

28:55.373 --> 28:59.566
So he says: we finally get back
together and she gets hit by a bus.

29:08.960 --> 29:10.858
This isn't a joke?

29:11.058 --> 29:15.752
No. My cousin's girlfriend
got hit by a bus last night.

29:16.750 --> 29:19.347
I'm sorry. How is she doing?

29:20.146 --> 29:22.446
She's got a broken leg.

29:28.238 --> 29:31.734
- Smooth, John, smooth.
- I thought it was a joke.

29:34.931 --> 29:36.530
What's so funny?

29:36.830 --> 29:39.627
- You had to be there.
- What've you got?

29:39.727 --> 29:43.921
Since your press conference last night
we've received about 50 calls.

29:44.220 --> 29:46.918
We've got people accusing everyone
from their mother-in-law to the mayor.

29:47.118 --> 29:48.817
Well, the mayor might not be
a bad lead.

29:49.016 --> 29:52.015
I got someone in my office you
guys should talk to.

29:52.513 --> 29:53.711
- Who is he?
- FBI profiler.

29:54.110 --> 29:56.708
- C'mon, Jack...
- OK, he's trying to help,

29:56.809 --> 29:59.604
...alright? This guy solved a lot of cases.
- What is he gonna tell me?

29:59.804 --> 30:01.202
I'm looking for a white male...

30:01.402 --> 30:04.400
- ... 25 to 45 years old?
- Just talk to him!

30:09.197 --> 30:10.896
Prudhomme, Hollinsworth,
agent Wingate.

30:11.095 --> 30:12.594
Nice to meet you.

30:14.789 --> 30:18.585
I understand you might
have something for us.

30:18.985 --> 30:21.183
Well, I thought maybe
I could help...

30:21.483 --> 30:23.381
...though I've never come across
a serial killer who's moved...

30:23.581 --> 30:25.080
...at such an accelerated pace.

30:25.480 --> 30:27.377
How do you know what pace
he's moving at?

30:27.578 --> 30:29.873
Your captain let me
look through the files.

30:30.073 --> 30:31.071
Did he?

30:31.571 --> 30:34.968
Based on what I've seen so far, you're looking
for someone of above average intelligence.

30:35.269 --> 30:38.066
White male, 25 to 45 years old...

30:40.664 --> 30:41.563
Something funny?

30:41.663 --> 30:44.657
- No, no. Go on.
- I'm sorry.

30:45.856 --> 30:48.454
He'll be middle class,
a loner, not married.

30:48.654 --> 30:51.651
Those who know him will
find him aloof but cordial.

30:51.951 --> 30:55.446
Although he prefers isolation,
he has the ability to navigate...

30:55.746 --> 30:56.846
...in social settings when he has to.

30:56.945 --> 31:00.441
He will have strong moral
and religious convictions.

31:00.840 --> 31:03.338
Obviously his moral convictions
don't include murder.

31:03.637 --> 31:05.637
He doesn't view what he's
doing as murder.

31:05.836 --> 31:08.834
To him, he's making
sacrifices to God.

31:09.533 --> 31:13.031
What point is there in keeping his
victims conscious while he mutilates them?

31:13.630 --> 31:15.526
Christ suffered on the cross.

31:15.726 --> 31:17.525
He wants his victims to suffer.

31:17.625 --> 31:20.521
But leaving clues behind
puts him at risk.

31:20.621 --> 31:22.019
He want us to know what he's doin'.

31:22.519 --> 31:23.919
True. But there's more
to it than that.

31:24.018 --> 31:26.016
If he merely wanted you
to know what he was doing...

31:26.051 --> 31:27.016
...there're more direct ways to inform you.

31:27.516 --> 31:29.913
The clues he leaves give
him a sense of power.

31:30.413 --> 31:32.707
And shows he's in control.

31:34.306 --> 31:37.004
Prudhomme, this fax just came in for you.
I think you should take a look at it.

31:39.701 --> 31:44.596
You have heard the voice of the prophet
as he prepares the throne of grace...

31:45.495 --> 31:48.092
...and you've twisted his message.

31:48.991 --> 31:52.488
Those who die, do so
for the glory of God.

31:52.788 --> 31:55.285
Spread the true gospel
before the end...

31:55.485 --> 32:00.381
of the Boanerges, or you shall
be judged by me.

32:00.880 --> 32:02.476
What makes you think this is him?

32:02.576 --> 32:03.375
Read the bottom.

32:04.574 --> 32:10.370
So you do not doubt... Inside
the third one is the key to the mount.

32:11.469 --> 32:13.568
May I? Third one?

32:14.567 --> 32:15.666
Ordway.

32:18.362 --> 32:20.260
Ordway, James.

32:21.159 --> 32:22.158
Come in.

32:22.655 --> 32:24.155
Where's Ordway's body?

32:24.255 --> 32:26.153
I just finished the autopsy.
I'm making out the report now.

32:26.353 --> 32:29.151
You can have it in... you can
have it by this afternoon.

32:29.450 --> 32:32.247
- Anything unusual?
- No. Not really.

32:33.246 --> 32:36.142
Except all he'd been
eating was olives.

32:36.341 --> 32:38.540
His stomach was full of them.

32:39.039 --> 32:41.637
- Mount of olives.
- It's him.

32:43.336 --> 32:44.434
See ya.

32:48.128 --> 32:49.728
This guy is fucking with us.

32:49.927 --> 32:52.324
He let you into his world
so you can publicise his work.

32:52.424 --> 32:54.823
He knows you know
what he's doing.

32:55.123 --> 32:57.020
Your failure to acknowledge it
has angered him.

32:57.220 --> 33:00.616
So he's going to kill again tomorrow
and there's nothing we can do to stop him.

33:01.116 --> 33:03.812
Can you run a search through
your database...

33:04.112 --> 33:06.110
...and see if you have anything
similar on file?

33:06.145 --> 33:08.109
No problem. Here's my direct
line at the Bureau...

33:08.309 --> 33:11.206
...and my cell phone number
will be on the back.

33:12.506 --> 33:14.904
Call me if there's anything I can do.

33:15.304 --> 33:16.703
Thank you.

33:38.677 --> 33:40.875
They've already got a name for him.

33:43.073 --> 33:44.373
It sells papers.

33:45.871 --> 33:47.768
What do you think makes
someone this crazy?

33:48.168 --> 33:49.765
Who knows?

33:49.865 --> 33:52.662
Problems mount,
pressures grow...

33:54.460 --> 33:57.159
One day you start to slip
through the cracks...

33:57.658 --> 33:59.854
...and there's no one there
to catch you.

34:00.754 --> 34:01.552
Happens every day.

34:01.952 --> 34:04.450
I'll tell you one thing for sure,
I'll feel a hell of a lot better...

34:04.649 --> 34:07.646
knowing that he's drooling on
himself in a padded cell somewhere.

34:09.344 --> 34:11.043
You're assuming we're
gonna catch him?

34:12.442 --> 34:14.041
What the hell's that
supposed to mean?

34:14.141 --> 34:15.442
Assuming we're
gonna catch him?

34:15.641 --> 34:19.137
It means that either we'll catch him or
he'll finish what he is doing...

34:19.335 --> 34:22.733
...and disappear like Jack the Ripper
and the Zodiac Killer.

34:23.032 --> 34:26.527
Or, come Easter, he'll realize all he has
is a rottin' corpse in his garage...

34:26.726 --> 34:28.627
So he'd figure he fucked up
his little recipe...

34:28.826 --> 34:31.024
...and start all over
again for next year.

34:32.223 --> 34:35.618
I don't know if he really believes
he's creating the second coming.

34:35.918 --> 34:38.014
I think it's more symbolic.

34:38.415 --> 34:40.413
He's sending a message.

34:40.713 --> 34:43.710
- Yeah? To whom?
- To us. The world.

34:44.010 --> 34:45.608
The guy is a fucking nutcase!

34:45.708 --> 34:48.007
All this religious mumbo jumbo
is bullshit!

34:48.206 --> 34:50.501
You don't think the guy is at home
right now, reading these headlines...

34:51.301 --> 34:53.498
...and jerking himself off?
He loves the attention...

34:53.533 --> 34:55.197
He wants the attention!

34:56.196 --> 34:58.595
I'm not doubting he's insane.

34:59.095 --> 35:01.890
But don't discount his intelligence.

35:02.590 --> 35:05.088
You think you just go out
and you find a 33 year old guy...

35:05.288 --> 35:07.882
...named Peter who happens
to be a fisherman?

35:08.982 --> 35:12.080
Or someone named Matthew
who is a tax collector?

35:12.879 --> 35:16.577
Don't you see planning
that's got into this? The time.

35:16.877 --> 35:20.173
Stop admiring him. He kills people.
Let's not lose sight of that.

35:20.373 --> 35:24.168
I admire the intellect,
not the action.

35:25.665 --> 35:28.762
Do you know how difficult
it is to get away with murder?

35:29.763 --> 35:32.460
There're 50 ways
to fuck up a crime.

35:33.060 --> 35:36.257
And if you can think of 20
of them you're a genius.

35:36.555 --> 35:39.352
So far, this guy is batting
a thousand.

36:07.621 --> 36:14.915
...just to find thy words...
... the faith of the son of God...

36:15.215 --> 36:22.009
Spread the true gospel before
the end of the... Boanerges...

36:22.308 --> 36:26.504
You shall be judged by him.

36:29.499 --> 36:31.298
Boanerges...

36:31.897 --> 36:35.393
From the Greek, sons of thunder...

36:35.593 --> 36:39.089
...an epithet used by Jesus.

36:39.388 --> 36:44.984
Sons of thunder...
Seems to be 2 people or more.

37:20.448 --> 37:21.548
Who is it?

37:22.646 --> 37:24.342
It's John Prudhomme!

37:28.938 --> 37:31.835
- John, it's very late.
- I'm sorry, Father.

37:31.935 --> 37:35.132
I need to talk to you,
it's important.

37:35.432 --> 37:37.329
- Well, come in.
- Thanks.

37:41.124 --> 37:41.923
Is everything alright?

37:42.223 --> 37:46.020
Yeah. I need some information
on the... Bonaerges.

37:46.219 --> 37:48.617
- The what?
- The Boa-ner-ges.

37:48.817 --> 37:50.617
Oh, it's pronounced Boa-ner-ges.

37:50.817 --> 37:55.508
Yeah, whatever. I... I know it
means sons of thunder.

37:55.808 --> 37:57.607
Whose sons?

37:57.907 --> 37:59.805
- Zebedee.
- Who is he?

38:00.105 --> 38:02.203
He's only mentioned in the Bible
in relation to his sons.

38:02.403 --> 38:05.101
- Yeah, where in the Bible?
- You should know this.

38:05.301 --> 38:08.897
Listen Father, I don't have time
for a Bible class right now.

38:09.196 --> 38:11.492
Well, come with me.

38:18.886 --> 38:20.484
Here it is.

38:30.074 --> 38:32.171
Mark, 3:17.

38:35.869 --> 38:39.665
James is son of Zebedee
and John, the brother of James...

38:39.765 --> 38:44.958
...and he surnamed them the Boanerges...
which is the sons of thunder.

38:45.757 --> 38:47.156
John, the brother of James?

38:48.555 --> 38:49.653
Yes.

38:49.753 --> 38:51.152
Thank you, Father.

38:53.550 --> 38:55.448
Ordway has a brother.
His name is John.

38:55.648 --> 38:59.242
He's going to be the fourth victim.
I need an address, fast. Thanks.

39:04.038 --> 39:06.237
John Ordway, photographer.
He has a work studio...

39:06.437 --> 39:08.434
- at 1432, Baker Street.
- Home address?

39:08.534 --> 39:10.533
The studio is
his home address.

39:10.633 --> 39:11.894
OK, I'm ten minutes away.

39:11.929 --> 39:14.527
Call him and tell him to lock himself in
and wait for me.

39:14.827 --> 39:16.226
I'll meet you there.

39:33.307 --> 39:35.607
I talked to him and told
him to lock himself in.

39:39.902 --> 39:42.898
Call for backup and
check the perimeter.

39:55.685 --> 39:58.879
Detective Hollinsworth requesting
backup at 1432, Baker Street.

42:10.344 --> 42:11.642
Hang on! Hang on!

42:13.840 --> 42:16.437
Oh God! Hang on!

42:18.034 --> 42:19.334
Hang on!

42:27.928 --> 42:29.226
Oh my God!

42:44.709 --> 42:46.410
God!

43:11.981 --> 43:14.877
I think he's still here.

43:30.363 --> 43:32.061
He's here! He's here!

44:06.823 --> 44:08.821
- Are you OK?
- He fucking got by me!

44:09.221 --> 44:10.520
Where did he go?

45:06.560 --> 45:07.958
Let's split up!

45:34.534 --> 45:37.430
- I want a 10-block perimeter set.
- I'm on it.

45:37.530 --> 45:38.628
Close the roof!

46:06.997 --> 46:09.794
You two take the alley.
We'll take the street!

46:44.259 --> 46:45.259
Freeze!

46:51.353 --> 46:52.850
Put your hands on your head!

46:53.850 --> 46:55.347
He's got a gun!

46:55.547 --> 46:56.446
Drop the weapon!
Drop the weapon, now!

47:00.443 --> 47:02.141
Put it down!

47:02.241 --> 47:04.939
Drop it and put up
your hands right now!

47:05.738 --> 47:07.136
Don't shoot!

47:19.522 --> 47:21.520
No! No! No!

47:21.921 --> 47:22.820
Shit!

47:23.318 --> 47:25.214
The gun was taped to his fuckin' hand!

47:25.314 --> 47:27.013
No!

47:28.413 --> 47:31.410
Get an ambulance!
Get an ambulance!

47:31.809 --> 47:34.409
- Take it easy!
- God!

47:36.307 --> 47:38.701
No! Oh, no!

47:42.500 --> 47:44.597
I can't... I can't feel my leg.

47:45.596 --> 47:46.995
- I can't feel my leg!
- Can't you give him something?

47:47.095 --> 47:48.394
- I did. It doesn't seem to work!
- I can't see my leg!

47:48.494 --> 47:49.792
- Can you see my leg?
- Hold on!

47:50.092 --> 47:52.491
We'll be at the hospital
in few minutes.

47:53.689 --> 47:57.882
Andy, 2 boys are sharing
the hospital room...

47:58.281 --> 48:03.978
...so, one boy asked the other
what he's there for...

48:04.376 --> 48:06.675
...so the boy says: circumcision...

48:07.474 --> 48:12.166
The other boy says: Oh man,
I'd that done right after I was born...

48:12.466 --> 48:15.463
...and I couldn't walk for a year.

48:16.563 --> 48:19.360
It was... It's the worst fucking
joke I ever heard, John.

48:22.157 --> 48:23.357
I know.

48:28.949 --> 48:31.048
- How are you, Jack?
- Sara.

48:31.348 --> 48:34.245
- How is he?
- We don't know yet.

48:45.733 --> 48:47.431
Bone's completely shattered.

48:47.531 --> 48:50.529
We've stopped the bleeding
but we'll have to amputate.

48:51.529 --> 48:53.826
There has to be something
else you can do.

48:54.226 --> 48:56.422
If there was, detective,
I'd be doing it.

49:18.899 --> 49:21.296
- Hey.
- Hey.

49:21.794 --> 49:25.392
- How you doin'?
- I'm OK.

49:28.486 --> 49:31.485
They wanna take my leg.
They wanna take my leg.

49:32.484 --> 49:33.783
I know.

49:34.583 --> 49:35.881
Don't let 'em take my leg.

49:36.981 --> 49:38.880
Please, don't let 'em take my leg.

49:40.078 --> 49:42.274
John, please, don't let 'em
take my leg!

49:46.869 --> 49:48.367
I'm scared. I'm scared.

49:50.066 --> 49:52.065
I'm... I'm scared!

50:31.921 --> 50:33.321
What the hell is he doing?

50:34.919 --> 50:38.917
It's a... an old Cajun superstition.

50:39.916 --> 50:43.210
When someone's suffering,
you put a knife under the bed...

50:44.110 --> 50:46.008
and... it cuts the pain in half.

51:03.389 --> 51:04.788
What are you doin' here?

51:05.687 --> 51:06.487
I'm working.

51:06.586 --> 51:08.784
John, go home. Get some rest.

51:09.185 --> 51:10.482
I'm not tired.

51:11.282 --> 51:12.280
In my office.

51:22.071 --> 51:25.566
John, I want you to
take a few days off.

51:25.766 --> 51:27.465
We can't waste any more time.

51:27.666 --> 51:29.661
That's really how you see it?
Isn't it?

51:29.861 --> 51:32.658
If you're not here, the rest of us are
just plodding along in the dark.

51:32.957 --> 51:35.457
- I didn't...
- You seeing those guys out there?

51:36.255 --> 51:37.954
Those are detectives.

51:38.454 --> 51:40.453
They do the same
job as you.

51:40.653 --> 51:42.152
I know that.

51:42.951 --> 51:46.546
I also know we
had him last night.

51:47.244 --> 51:51.539
He was standing in the
same room with me. And got away.

51:52.339 --> 51:54.237
Don't take me off this, Jack.

51:57.334 --> 51:58.133
Alright.

51:59.433 --> 52:00.430
Thanks.

52:01.528 --> 52:04.726
What do you think he's gonna do?
I mean, you interrupted him last night.

52:04.926 --> 52:06.524
He didn't get what he came for.

52:07.723 --> 52:10.721
If he wants to stay
on schedule for Easter...

52:11.120 --> 52:13.616
He's gonna have to
make up for lost time.

52:14.416 --> 52:15.613
So are you.

52:20.408 --> 52:21.307
John.

52:23.107 --> 52:26.901
- We just want you to know that...
- Thanks guys.

52:27.001 --> 52:28.200
Thank you.

52:43.688 --> 52:46.582
There's a Dr. Nestler
on line one for you.

52:48.682 --> 52:51.378
- Hi, doctor.
- We've a problem over here...

52:51.478 --> 52:53.175
...that I thought you
should know about.

52:53.275 --> 52:55.374
I thought the operation
went fine.

52:55.674 --> 52:56.972
It did.

52:57.472 --> 52:59.870
I... I don't understand.

53:00.069 --> 53:03.763
One of our orderlies was
found unconscious down there.

53:04.063 --> 53:05.462
Someone beat the hell out of him.

53:05.661 --> 53:08.759
- I'll send an officer over.
- The police are already here.

53:08.959 --> 53:10.058
Detective...

53:10.158 --> 53:13.455
The orderly was carrying
an appendage downstairs.

53:13.955 --> 53:16.351
Somebody stole your partner's leg.

53:27.538 --> 53:28.538
Can I see him?

53:28.738 --> 53:31.836
He's still pretty groggy.
Try not to be long.

53:32.034 --> 53:33.231
Thanks.

53:50.617 --> 53:54.811
I wanted to stop by
and see how you were doing.

53:58.010 --> 53:59.308
You need anything?

54:00.506 --> 54:03.003
Yeah. A leg.

54:04.102 --> 54:05.500
You got one?

54:08.297 --> 54:10.095
I'm sorry.

54:12.394 --> 54:13.593
I'm so sorry.

54:15.891 --> 54:19.885
Hey, you know... When I was
coming out of the alley...

54:22.681 --> 54:27.576
I was... I was...
I could hear you screaming.

54:29.374 --> 54:33.770
I just... I never imagined that
you were screaming at me.

54:34.668 --> 54:40.663
I must have been pretty out of it,
from the stunt gun.

54:42.161 --> 54:44.160
I just get...

54:44.961 --> 54:47.458
I just get moving towards
the sound of your voice.

54:55.047 --> 54:56.946
I love being a cop.

54:59.446 --> 55:01.642
It's all I ever wanted to be.

55:02.042 --> 55:04.141
Far back as I can remember.

55:04.439 --> 55:08.733
A cop.
Helping people.

55:10.033 --> 55:12.031
Righting wrongs.

55:13.030 --> 55:15.528
You know what I mean?
That's the finest thing you can be.

55:18.824 --> 55:21.721
Oh man... Oh man...

55:22.021 --> 55:24.917
What am I gonna do now, John?

55:26.615 --> 55:28.913
What am I gonna do now?

55:36.104 --> 55:38.801
You can go, you know?
You can go.

55:39.702 --> 55:41.999
I just want to be
left alone, alright?

55:43.299 --> 55:44.397
Go on. Go!

56:11.468 --> 56:13.967
- Wingate.
- John Prudhomme.

56:17.963 --> 56:19.561
Thank you.

56:20.061 --> 56:22.256
You’re lettin' him inside your
head. You can't do that.

56:22.757 --> 56:25.054
How am I not to do that?

56:25.453 --> 56:27.652
You divorce yourself from
the emotions.

56:27.951 --> 56:28.951
What?

56:30.251 --> 56:33.146
Turn it off like a light switch?

56:33.745 --> 56:35.644
Right now, there is a cop...

56:36.841 --> 56:38.739
a friend...

56:39.338 --> 56:41.538
Who will never be the same
because of me.

56:41.737 --> 56:43.435
You're doing exactly
what he wants you to do.

56:43.535 --> 56:44.635
You're concentrating on your guilt.

56:44.835 --> 56:48.532
I got my fucking partner
shot last night!

56:48.932 --> 56:51.428
What the fuck are you
looking at?

56:55.424 --> 56:57.521
How can I help you,
Prudhomme?

56:57.720 --> 56:59.819
I assume there are others
you can talk to...

57:00.019 --> 57:03.116
